      title: 'Philosophical Foundation',
      content: `These writings are grounded in the intellectual tradition of Austrian economics and classical liberalism, drawing particularly from the works of Ludwig von Mises, Murray Rothbard, and Friedrich Hayek. The central insight is that human freedom and voluntary cooperation are not just moral imperatives but practical necessities for human flourishing.`,
